
// The code snippet demonstrates how to add nodes from the [.arguments] node set to the [args] node within a [sockets.signal] invocation. It uses the [add] slot to append nodes and the [get-nodes] slot to retrieve nodes from the [.arguments] node set. This allows for dynamic construction of arguments for a SignalR signal based on the current context.
add:x:./*/sockets.signal/*/args
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
